.TH "NAVIGATIONHISTORYENTRY.ID" "3JS" "December 8, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
NavigationHistoryEntry.id \- NavigationHistoryEntry: id property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]id\f[B]\f[R] read\-only property of the
\f[CR]NavigationHistoryEntry\f[R] interface returns the \f[CR]id\f[R] of
the history entry, or an empty string if current document is not fully
active.
This is a unique, UA\-generated value that always represents a specific
history entry, useful to correlate it with an external resource such as
a storage cache.
.PP
This differs from the \f[CR]key\f[R] of a history entry.
The \f[CR]key\f[R] is a unique, UA\-generated value that represents the
history entry\(cqs slot in the entries list rather than the entry
itself.
It is used to navigate that particular slot via
\f[CR]Navigation.traverseTo()\f[R].
The \f[CR]key\f[R] will be reused by other entries that replace the
entry in the list (that is, if the
\f[CR]NavigateEvent.navigationType\f[R] is \f[CR]replace\f[R]).
.SH VALUE
A string representing the \f[CR]id\f[R] of the
\f[CR]NavigationHistoryEntry\f[R].
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] current = navigation.currentEntry;
console.log(current.id);
.EE
